In the time of monsoons.. many parts of India are vulnerable to monsoon floods as well. Here's a story from Uttarakhand highlighting how the proud mountain people work together to repair their flood-damaged roads with Goonj.

Creating a space for women's hygiene in a community is also claiming a space and voice for women, for a human need. Goonj nudged the men and women of a small village in Tamil Nadu to celebrate Menstrual Hygiene Day for the first time. They came together to make this space for their women. Goonj has been working through the years, to mobilize and motivate women to priortise their menstrual hygiene needs by creating safe spaces, kitchen gardens and taking many other action projects in their own communities. This year Goonj celebrated Menstrual Hygiene Week with thousands of women in the villages of India.. 
Menstruation is a human issue, not just a women's issue..

Women of rural Odisha celebrate Menstrual Hygiene Week  with action and dialogue. Watch this video to know more about how they opened up dialogue, spread awareness and mobilized women to take action against their unresolved issues. To know more, write to us: njpc@goonj.org

Today is World #MenstrualHygieneDay. This year, to mark #MenstrualHygieneDay, Team Goonj decided to convert the day into a week long celebrations with over 4000 women across the villages of 10 states. In the coming week we will be sharing updates on how women in the villages across India celebrated and said about menstruation. Meanwhile do take the time today, to talk to a woman in your network about her menstrual challenges. Let's acknowledge and mainstream menstruation as a human issue, not just a women's issue. We strive to break the stigma that surrounds menstrual health, normalize open dialogue around it and develop comprehensive solutions on the ground and at the policy level.

Stay tuned for more information about the dialogues and activities that took place during this week throughout the country.

To know more about Goonj’s work on MHM log on to 
Link to NJPC facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/njpc.goonj
Link to NJPC website page: https://goonj.org/njpc/

In Assam and West Bengal, lakhs of people are living through something we don’t talk about enough the aftermath of a disaster.
The water may stop rising after a point, but the everyday struggle to rebuild—with little or nothing—has already begun.

In West Bengal, 2 lakh+ people across 188 villages are wading through submerged homes and broken routines.
Source- https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/west-bengal/two-lakh-people-affected-by-ghatal-floods-thousands-evacuated-west-bengal-minister/article69732576.ece

In Assam, vast areas are once again waterlogged—cutting off villages, washing away essentials, and turning survival into a daily negotiation.
But this isn’t just about floodwaters.
It’s about the silence that follows.

When families return to soaked homes and washed-away memories.
When a schoolbag, a grain sack, or even a dry place to sleep becomes a distant hope.

When resilience shows up in the smallest acts—staying, cleaning, waiting—for help that may or may not come.

At Goonj, through Rahat, we stay for this after.
Not to give, but to walk alongside.
Because in the quiet, long shadow of a disaster, what people need most—is to not be forgotten.

How You Can Be Part of This
You can help ensure families don’t face this alone:
Contribute material – clean, usable essentials

Support our Rahat efforts – your contribution helps reach where headlines don’t
https://goonj.org/donate/campaign/rahat-old

Let’s turn empathy into action.
Because rebuilding with dignity isn’t a one-time act—it’s a shared responsibility.

In a village in Karnataka, where floods had become an annual disaster, 100 people came together — not to wait, but to act.

With support from Goonj’s Cloth for Work and Rahat, they cleared a clogged canal that once fed their fields.

The water returned. And with it — dignity.

This is what community-led climate resilience looks like.

As monsoons intensify across India, you can stand with communities like Tigadi.

Support Rahat, Goonj’s dignified disaster response initiative.
Contribute now: https://goonj.org/donate/campaign/rahat-old

After the floods recede, the quiet work of rebuilding begins—restoring routines, reclaiming spaces, and reviving everyday dignity.

In Yadahalli village, Bagalkote district (Karnataka), this rebuilding began with a vital space: the Primary Health Centre. After the monsoon, the area around it was filled with stagnant water and waste. But the people of Yadahalli—including many from the Devadasi and daily wage communities—didn’t wait. They came together with intent, local tools, and collective resolve.

Yadahalli’s story reminds us: recovery isn’t just about rebuilding structures—it’s about nurturing what people already hold—resilience, wisdom, and the will to act.

This monsoon season, as floods and landslides return to many parts of the country, stand with the community.

Contribute at https://goonj.org/donate/campaign/rahat-old

Call for Submissions
Special Issue on Menstrual Health and Hygiene

The @cdpp.india in collaboration with @goonj, invites submissions for a Special Issue to be launched at the Menstruation Dialogue 2026.

We seek original contributions that explore menstruation as a public health, gender justice, and development issue. Submissions can include academic research, field-based case studies, interviews, and visual essays.

Suggested themes include:
– Structural inequalities (caste, class, disability, gender identity)
– WASH infrastructure and access
– Menstrual health in education and the workplace
– Climate change, crisis response, and sustainability
– Grassroots innovations and policy frameworks

Abstracts (300–400 words) are due by August 1, 2025. Full submission guidelines and themes are available on our website.

For details, check our MHH 2026 highlight or visit www.cdpp.co.in/events/menstruation-dialogue-2025-26-call-for-submissions

What if you could be part of the change we all hope for?

The world doesn’t need heroes — it needs listeners, learners, and doers.
People who are ready to walk with communities, not ahead of them.

The Goonj Setu Fellowship is not about leading, but about connecting.
Not to instruct, but to listen.
Not to fix, but to walk alongside.

Become a bridge — between urban and rural, resourceful and resource-constrained, awareness and action.
Through immersive, pan-India fieldwork, co-create grassroots solutions on menstrual dignity, climate resilience, disaster response, and more — with the people living these realities every day.

This isn’t just a fellowship.
It’s a journey to unlearn, relearn, and understand your country —
to be part of something bigger than yourself.

Be the Setu. Build trust. Enable change. Walk together.

latestPosts.caption:
Urgent Action Needed – Rahat Floods 

The monsoon has set in, and with it, floods and landslides have disrupted lives across multiple regions in India—displacing families, damaging homes, and affecting livelihoods.
Goonj is on the ground, responding with our teams and grassroots partners. But as the situation unfolds, the scale of need is growing rapidly.
Your immediate support can help us reach more people, faster.

What You Can Contribute

Material Contributions (Urgent Needs):
-Dry ration, ready-to-eat food
-Blankets, tarpaulins, mosquito nets
-Sanitary pads, general medicines
-Utensils, slippers, umbrellas
-Raincoats, wearable clothing (all age groups)
-Torches, batteries

📍 Find your nearest dropping centre:
 👉 https://goonj.org/dropping-centres/

 Monetary Contributions
 Support the transportation and procurement of essential relief supplies.
 👉 https://goonj.org/donate/campaign/rahat-old

Other Ways to Stand with Affected Communities
 Organize a Collection Camp
 Host a drive in your home, office, school, college, or community.
 👉 https://goonj.org/collection-camps/

Start Payroll Giving
 Enable employees to contribute a small part of their salary for relief efforts.
 👉 https://crm.goonj.org/contribute/website-user/

Every contribution—big or small—makes a difference.
 Let’s respond together with urgency and empathy.
📧 mail@goonj.org | 📞 011-41401216

#Rahat #FloodRelief2025 #RespondWithGoonj #ActWithEmpathy #MaterialMatters #EveryBitCounts
